title: Grateful Dead Live at Oakland-Alameda County Coliseum on 1985-12-31
description: Not Fade Away-> Touch Of Gray, Tons Of Steel, CC Rider, Dupree's Diamond Blues, Cassidy-> Brown Eyed Women, Let It Grow Midnight Hour-> Sugaree, Women Are Smarter, Ship of Fools, Playin' In The Band-> Terrapin Station-> Drums*-> Truckin'-> Black Peter-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E:Not Fade Away-> E: Turn On Your Love Light, E: Brokedown Palace*

reviews.review_text:
Very decent sound quality In my opinion this is the best sounding of the three listed. There are flaws to be sure, the Terrapin intro is disappointing but all in all its decent quality and I really enjoy the first set. NFA>Touch is pretty cool. The Cassidy and Brown-Eyed Women are smoking. If you are looking for a decent recording of the New Year's Eve show I think this is worth the download.

12-7-09 UPDATE

The Charlie Miller soundboard that has been added after this one is by far the best sounding recording from this night. It might be one of the best sounding shows on this site.

Don't be fooled! This is if not the worst, definite one of the worst New Year's shows ever! I'm sorry if you think you it was good, but please compare others such as 81-82 (best ever) for example, or even the closing of Winterland is much better than this. They get progressively worse after '82.
